<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD//XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Column boxes do not establish containing blocks for fixed positioning</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-multicol/#the-multi-column-model"/>
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Column boxes that contain the static position of a fixed positioned element do not create a containing block. Fixed positioned elements are positioned based on the viewport." />
        <style type="text/css">
            html, body
            {
                padding: 0;
                margin: 0;
            }
            p
            {
                margin-left: 8px;
            }
            div
            {
                column-count: 2;
                column-width: 5em;
                column-gap: 1em;
            }
            div
            {
                background: green;
                color: green;
                font: 20px/1 ahem;
                height: 6em;
                position: relative;
                width: 11em;
            }
            span
            {
                color: red;
            }
            #span2
            {
                color: green;
                position: fixed;
                left: 2em;
                width: 2em;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if there is no red visible on the page.</p>
        <div>
            XXXXX XXXXX XXXXX XXXXX XXXXX XXXXX XXXXX XXXXX XX<span>XX</span>X XXX<span id="span2">XX XX</span> XX<span>XX</span>X XXX
        </div>
    </body>
</html>